            "answer_text": "Standard PCR uses dNTP\u2019s. DNA sequencing by the Sanger method uses dideoxy NTP's as a chain terminator. The ratio of dNTP to ddNTP is calculated such that on average one ddNTP is incorporated once per strand synthesis by DNA polymerase. ",
